# SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
#
# Disable Annex K (C11 bounded string APIs like fprintf_s, memcpy_s) checks:
# glibc does not implement these, they are optional, and clang-tidy's insistence
# generates noise on every fprintf/snprintf/memcpy call. Standard Linux C code
# uses bounded-buffer discipline at the caller site (we do: explicit lengths
# via snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), ...)), not Annex K.
Checks: '-clang-analyzer-security.insecureAPI.DeprecatedOrUnsafeBufferHandling'
